Word is that Malusi Gigaba’s lawyers are seeking to keep Norma Mngoma's testimony under wraps at the State Capture Commission. Melusi Xulu, attorney with Donda attorneys,discusses this. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The estranged wife of former minister Malusi Gigaba is set to testify at the State Capture Commission on Friday. Gigaba, however, doesn't want Norma Mngoma's testimony made public. READ: Norma Mngoma agrees to testify at State Capture Inquiry Lawyer, Melusi Xulu, explains who will have the final say on whether Mngoma's testimony is muzzled, or not. Mngoma was arrested last year for allegedly trashing a car. The charges were dropped. Watch the video above for more details.